** Talent International **   
  
We are excited to be working with a major Queensland Government frontline
department seeking a Power Apps Developer.

** Scope of Position **

  
We are seeking a suitably experienced Power Apps Developer and Administrator,
to join the team to contribute to the successful delivery of the various
projects allocated to the Agencies Directorate.

** YOU WILL ** be a member of the IST Directorate - Technology Transition Team and will receive advice and guidance from the Directorate's Technology Transition Implementation Lead, Data Centre SME, Solution Architects and Project Managers, as required. 

** YOU WILL ** be assigned to work on a range of different projects over the duration of the engagement, and may be required to work concurrently on multiple projects. 

** YOU WILL ** use Agile methodology and be working with business representative/s, analysts and testers to deliver required changes. 

All projects have a Project Manager who follows an approved project
methodology and reports to a governance board.

** Key Accountabilities & Skills **

Work collaboratively with a team of information technology professionals and
participate in the analysis, design, build and delivery of information
technology systems and services for the provision of effective Information and
** Communication ** Technology (ICT) solutions.

Delivering services and solutions on behalf of QPS as part of the Directorate
using the suite of Microsoft's PowerApps, Power BI, Power Automate Flow,
SharePoint, Microsoft Teams, custom development, and data integrations on the
platform.

Analyse and provide solutions to complex technical problems to ensure ICT
performance outcomes meets service level requirements.

** **

** ESSENTIAL **

Extensive experience developing services and solutions using the Microsoft
Power Platform.

Microsoft 365 Tenancy Administration Services (including Exchange Online,
Teams, OneDrive, OneNote, Sharepoint)

Active Directory (2012, 2016), ADFS, Azure AD

Scripting (including PowerShell for administration of Azure AD, MS Online
Services)

** DESIRABLE **

A strong understanding of corporate enterprise environments and expectations
to support the delivery of rubust and secure solutions.

Strong understanding of the IT&T industry, as well as technology trends and
related practices

Basic network experience - administration - basic switches, router, and
firewalls

